The paper deals with graph algorithms for network analysis, which is a topic that falls under several CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper presents two algorithms for solving graph problems. The second likely category is cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) since the paper deals with network analysis. The third likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry) since the paper deals with finding paths and distances in graphs. The fourth likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) since the paper deals with graph theory. The fifth likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) since the paper deals with finding optimal solutions in graphs.
